BINARY SEARCH
=> IT CAN BE ONLY APPLICABLE ON THE SORTED ARRAY . DOES NOT MATTER IF SORTED IN ASCENDING OR DESCENDING
STEPS OF EXECUTION -:
1} FIND THE MIDDLE TERM OF THE ARRAY
2} FIND IF TARGET < MIDDLE TERM , SEARCH IN LEFT SIDE OF THE ARRAY ELSE SEARCH IN RIGHT OF THE MIDDLE TERM
3} IF MIDDLE TERM == TARGET THE YOU FOUND THE ELEMENT


BEST CASE = O(n)
WORST CAST = O(log n)

=> WHEN WE ARE GOING APPLY BINARY SEARCH ON THE ARRAY SORTED IN DESCENDING ORDER WE MAKE SURE TO CHECK SOME OF THE CONDITIONS.


ORDER AGNOSTIC BINARY SEARCH
=> WHEN WE DONT KNOW THAT THE ARRAY IS SORTED OR NOT






